scmPrintMIB.name: scmPrintMIB
scmPrintMIB.organization: Samsung Common Management Interface Working Group
scmPrintMIB.description: Version: 1.00 Samsung SCMI Extension to IETF Printer MIB Module. This Module provides extension to the IETF Printer MIB. Copyright (C) 2003-2004 Samsung Corporation. All Rights Reserved.

scmPrtBaseTable.name: scmPrtBaseTable
scmPrtBaseTable.description: A table of general counters and information for ease of use of the SCMI Extension to IETF Printer MIB Module and the IETF Printer MIB on this host system. Usage: The ONLY valid row in the 'scmPrtBaseTable' shall ALWAYS have an 'scmPrtBaseIndex' of one ('1').

scmPrtBaseEntry.name: scmPrtBaseEntry
scmPrtBaseEntry.description: An entry of general counters and information for ease of use of the SCMI Extension to IETF Printer MIB Module and the IETF Printer MIB on this host system. Usage: The ONLY valid row in the 'scmPrtBaseTable' shall ALWAYS have an 'scmPrtBaseIndex' of one ('1').

scmPrtBaseIndex.name: scmPrtBaseIndex
scmPrtBaseIndex.description: A unique value used by this host system to identify this conceptual row in the 'scmPrtBaseTable'. Usage: The ONLY valid row in the 'scmPrtBaseTable' shall ALWAYS have an 'scmPrtBaseIndex' of one ('1').

scmPrtBaseRowStatus.name: scmPrtBaseRowStatus
scmPrtBaseRowStatus.description: This object is used to display status of the ONLY valid conceptual row in the 'scmPrtBaseTable'. Usage: 'scmPrtBaseRowStatus' is 'read-only' because the ONLY valid conceptual row shall NOT be deleted.

scmPrtMIBCompliance.name: scmPrtMIBCompliance
scmPrtMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents that implement the printer MIB extension module.

scmPrtGeneralPrnModelName.name: scmPrtGeneralPrnModelName
scmPrtGeneralPrnModelName.description: Represent the printer model name currently being connected with NPC.

scmPrtGeneralTable.name: scmPrtGeneralTable
scmPrtGeneralTable.description: A table of general information per printer. This table augments the prtGeneralTable.

scmPrtGeneralEntry.name: scmPrtGeneralEntry
scmPrtGeneralEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each device entry in the hostmib device table whose type is printer.

scmPrtGeneralRowStatus.name: scmPrtGeneralRowStatus
scmPrtGeneralRowStatus.description: Manages the status of this conceptual row in the scmPrtGeneralTable.

scmPrtInputTraySwitch.name: scmPrtInputTraySwitch
scmPrtInputTraySwitch.description: if language is set to AUTO, this options can the printer anlyzes the stream of data being sent to determine which language is being used by the printer job, and the printer's emulation language automatically be switched if this options is set.

scmPrtInputLockTray.name: scmPrtInputLockTray
scmPrtInputLockTray.description: Trays and combination trays can be locked out of the paper selection process. The available options depend on the configuration of MP tray.

scmPrtInputTable.name: scmPrtInputTable
scmPrtInputTable.description: This table logically augments the Printer MIB's prtInputTable.

scmPrtInputEntry.name: scmPrtInputEntry
scmPrtInputEntry.description: Entries may exist for each entry in the prtInputTable.

scmPrtInputRowStatus.name: scmPrtInputRowStatus
scmPrtInputRowStatus.description: Manages the status of this conceptual row in the scmPrtInputTable.

scmPrtInputNextPrtInputIndex.name: scmPrtInputNextPrtInputIndex
scmPrtInputNextPrtInputIndex.description: The value of prtInputIndex corresponding to the input subunit which will be used when this input subunit is emptied. The value of zero indicates that auto input switching will not occur when this input subunit is emptied. Two different mechanisms for input tray switching, scmPrtNextPrtInputIndex and scmPrtInputAliasGroup, are provided. A device agent may make use of one or the other, none, or both. Use the model that fits best for the given application. Usage: Conforming management agents, which ALSO implement the the Printer MIB v2, SHALL set 'scmPrtInputNextPrtInputIndex' to the SAME value as 'prtInputNextIndex' (i.e., the values of these two objects SHALL be interlocked).

scmPrtInputUseCustomSize.name: scmPrtInputUseCustomSize
scmPrtInputUseCustomSize.description: Specifies how this input subunit determines the paper size to use. If the value is 'Off' this input subunit uses the paper size automatically sensed by the subunit. If the value is 'On' this input subunit uses the custom dimensions provided by scmPrtInputCustDimFeedDirDecl and scmPrtInputCustDimXFeedDirDecl.

scmPrtInputCustDimFeedDirDecl.name: scmPrtInputCustDimFeedDirDecl
scmPrtInputCustDimFeedDirDecl.description: Provides the dimension, in the feed direction, of the media in this input subunit, when the value of scmPrtInputUseCustomSize is set to 'On'. When scmPrtInputUseCustomSize is set to On, this value is copied to prtInputMediaDimFeedDirDeclared and prtInputMediaDimFeedDirChosen.

scmPrtInputCustDimXFeedDirDecl.name: scmPrtInputCustDimXFeedDirDecl
scmPrtInputCustDimXFeedDirDecl.description: Provides the dimension, in the feed direction, of the media in this input subunit, when the value of scmPrtInputUseCustomSize is set to 'On'. When scmPrtInputUseCustomSize is set to 'On', this value is copied to prtInputMediaDimFeedDirDeclared and prtInputMediaDimFeedDirChosen.

scmPrtInputTrayPriority.name: scmPrtInputTrayPriority
scmPrtInputTrayPriority.description: The current priority of this tray. This value/mechanism is independent of scmPrtNextPrtInputIndex and scmPrtInputAliasGroup. Usage: The priority of this device, where '0' is unspecified (default), '1' is lowest, and '100' is highest.

scmPrtInputPaperSize.name: scmPrtInputPaperSize
scmPrtInputPaperSize.description: Value of Paper size for printing. Some printer such like ML6060 or Modena have a 4 bytes data length. So, to distinguish these models we have to check model id or version.

scmPrtInputPaperSizeOptions.name: scmPrtInputPaperSizeOptions
scmPrtInputPaperSizeOptions.description: Paper size options that are available in this model. Some printer such like ML6060 or Modena have a 4 bytes data length. So, to distinguish these models we have to check model id or version.

scmPrtInputTrayNum.name: scmPrtInputTrayNum
scmPrtInputTrayNum.description: It can select the type of paper tray. The types of tray can be varied according to the printer model

scmPrtOutputTable.name: scmPrtOutputTable
scmPrtOutputTable.description: This table logically augments the prtOutputTable in the Printer MIB.

scmPrtOutputEntry.name: scmPrtOutputEntry
scmPrtOutputEntry.description: Entries may exist for each entry in the prtOutputTable.

scmPrtOutputRowStatus.name: scmPrtOutputRowStatus
scmPrtOutputRowStatus.description: Manages the status of this conceptual row in the scmPrtOutputTable.

scmPrtOutputNextIndex.name: scmPrtOutputNextIndex
scmPrtOutputNextIndex.description: The value of prtOutputIndex corresponding to the output subunit which will be used when this output subunit is filled. A value of zero(0) indicates that auto output switching will not occur when this output subunit is filled.

scmPrtOutputPassword.name: scmPrtOutputPassword
scmPrtOutputPassword.description: This object is used as the password for an Output Tray, e.g. an output mailbox. It is the value that must be entered to open the output tray.

scmPrtOutputOffsetStackingType.name: scmPrtOutputOffsetStackingType
scmPrtOutputOffsetStackingType.description: This object further refines the type of offset stacking from that specified by the object prtOutputOffsetStacking in the Printer MIB.

scmPrtOutputTrayTimeoutSupport.name: scmPrtOutputTrayTimeoutSupport
scmPrtOutputTrayTimeoutSupport.description: Determines whether the printer should wait before sending the printed output to another output destination when the selected or default destination is full. 'On' indicates that would should wait as specified by scmPrtOutputTrayTimeout. 'Off' indicates this feature is off and should immediately seek to send the printed output to another destination. The value 'other' shall mean not specified.

scmPrtOutputTrayTimeout.name: scmPrtOutputTrayTimeout
scmPrtOutputTrayTimeout.description: Determines how long the printer should wait before sending the printed output to another output destination when the selected or default destination is full. A value of (0) implies 'other' or 'infinite' which translates to this input subunit does not support this feature.

scmPrtOutputFinishier.name: scmPrtOutputFinishier
scmPrtOutputFinishier.description: This object declares the printer output finishier.

scmPrtOutputFinishierOptions.name: scmPrtOutputFinishierOptions
scmPrtOutputFinishierOptions.description: This object declares the printer output finishier option. options 1. staple 2. punch

scmPrtChannelTable.name: scmPrtChannelTable
scmPrtChannelTable.description: This table logically augments Printer MIB's prtChannelTable.

scmPrtChannelEntry.name: scmPrtChannelEntry
scmPrtChannelEntry.description: An entry exists corresponding to each entry in the prtChannelTable.

scmPrtChannelRowStatus.name: scmPrtChannelRowStatus
scmPrtChannelRowStatus.description: Manages the status of this conceptual row in the scmPrtChannelTable.

scmPrtChannelEOJTimeout.name: scmPrtChannelEOJTimeout
scmPrtChannelEOJTimeout.description: Defines the number of seconds that the channel waits before timing out. For example, this may be used for the parallel channel. The value zero means infinite or no timeout on the channel.

scmPrtInterpreterCopyNum.name: scmPrtInterpreterCopyNum
scmPrtInterpreterCopyNum.description: It can select how many papers are printed Normally it can be selected 1- 999.

scmPrtInterpreterTable.name: scmPrtInterpreterTable
scmPrtInterpreterTable.description: This table logically augments the Printer MIB's prtInterpreterTable.

scmPrtInterpreterEntry.name: scmPrtInterpreterEntry
scmPrtInterpreterEntry.description: An entry exists corresponding to each entry in the prtInterpreterTable.

scmPrtInterpRowStatus.name: scmPrtInterpRowStatus
scmPrtInterpRowStatus.description: Manages the status of this conceptual row in the scmPrtInterpreterTable.

scmPrtInterpJobCopiesDefault.name: scmPrtInterpJobCopiesDefault
scmPrtInterpJobCopiesDefault.description: This defines the default number of job copies to be printed by this interpreter. If set incorrectly, this object may cause difficulties at customer sites. Agent developers should consider making this object read-only, permanently set to one copy.

scmPrtInterpLineTerm.name: scmPrtInterpLineTerm
scmPrtInterpLineTerm.description: Enables adding a Carriage Return after every Line Feed. The value 'On' indicates that a Carriage Return will be added after every Line Feed. Usage example: This is a useful feature when printing text jobs via PCL through a standard queue in UNIX. The value 'other' shall mean not specified.

scmPrtInterpProcessBarcodes.name: scmPrtInterpProcessBarcodes
scmPrtInterpProcessBarcodes.description: Specifies whether the 'extra' barcode processing within the interpreter should be used.

scmPrtInterpOrientation.name: scmPrtInterpOrientation
scmPrtInterpOrientation.description: It determines the direction of the print image on the page. The first two kinds of options are portrait(tall) and landscape(wide). reversePortrait is 180 degrees rotation of portrait. reverseLandscape is 180 degrees rotation of landscape.

scmPrtMarkerSrt.name: scmPrtMarkerSrt
scmPrtMarkerSrt.description: It determin Samsung Resolution Technology option when it is ON.

scmPrtMarkerDensity.name: scmPrtMarkerDensity
scmPrtMarkerDensity.description: It determines the overall density of page

scmPrtMarkerSmetMode.name: scmPrtMarkerSmetMode
scmPrtMarkerSmetMode.description: The value of this object indicates whether the SMET mode is currently enabled.

scmPrtMarkerSmetModeOptions.name: scmPrtMarkerSmetModeOptions
scmPrtMarkerSmetModeOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for smetMode in this printer.

scmPrtMarkerduplexTopMargin.name: scmPrtMarkerduplexTopMargin
scmPrtMarkerduplexTopMargin.description: The value of this object gives the top margin on the backside of a page when printing in duplex mode. The actual value used in the printer is the value of this object divided by 10. The unit is inch.

scmPrtMarkerduplexLeftMargin.name: scmPrtMarkerduplexLeftMargin
scmPrtMarkerduplexLeftMargin.description: The value of this object gives the left margin on the backside of a page when printing in duplex mode. The actual value used in the printer is the value of this object divided by 10. The unit is inch.

scmPrtMarkerShortEdgeBindingMargin.name: scmPrtMarkerShortEdgeBindingMargin
scmPrtMarkerShortEdgeBindingMargin.description: The value of this object gives the margin left for binding on the short edge of the paper when printing is done in short edge duplex mode. The actual value used in the printer is the value of this object divided by 10. The unit is inch.

scmPrtMarkerLongEdgeBindingMargin.name: scmPrtMarkerLongEdgeBindingMargin
scmPrtMarkerLongEdgeBindingMargin.description: The value of this object gives the margin left for binding on the long edge of the paper when printing is done in long edge duplex mode. The actual value used in the printer is the value of this object divided by 10. The unit is inch.

scmPrtMarkerTonerSave.name: scmPrtMarkerTonerSave
scmPrtMarkerTonerSave.description: Echo mode option. Echo mode Off Echo mode On

scmPrtMarkerTonerOutAction.name: scmPrtMarkerTonerOutAction
scmPrtMarkerTonerOutAction.description: The value of this object gives the action taken by the printer when the tonerLow condition occurs. If the value is continue(1), the printer continues to print in spite of the toner being low. If the value is stop(2), the printer stops printing when the toner is low.

scmPrtMarkerTonerOutActionOptions.name: scmPrtMarkerTonerOutActionOptions
scmPrtMarkerTonerOutActionOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for tonerLowAction in this printer.

scmPrtMarkerEntry.name: scmPrtMarkerEntry
scmPrtMarkerEntry.description: Entries may exist in the table for each device index who's device type is printer

scmPrtMarkerResolution.name: scmPrtMarkerResolution
scmPrtMarkerResolution.description: The value of this object gives the current resolution used while printing. The value res300(1) means 300X300 dpi resolution. The value res600(2) means 600X600 dpi resolution. The value res1200(4) means 1200X1200 dpi resolution.

scmPrtMarkerResolutionOptions.name: scmPrtMarkerResolutionOptions
scmPrtMarkerResolutionOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of all the supported values for resolution in this printer.

scmPrtOperarionMenuClear.name: scmPrtOperarionMenuClear
scmPrtOperarionMenuClear.description: When the value of this object is set to clearMenus(1), the values of all the printer properties in all the menus will be set to default values.

scmPrtOperationMenuClearOptions.name: scmPrtOperationMenuClearOptions
scmPrtOperationMenuClearOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for menuClear in this printer.

scmPrtOperationFuserClean.name: scmPrtOperationFuserClean
scmPrtOperationFuserClean.description: When the value of this object is set to fuserClean(2),the printer fuser will be clear

scmPrtOperationFuserCleanOptions.name: scmPrtOperationFuserCleanOptions
scmPrtOperationFuserCleanOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for nfuserClean in this printer.

scmPrtOperationOpcClean.name: scmPrtOperationOpcClean
scmPrtOperationOpcClean.description: When the value of this object is set to opcClean(2),the printer OPC will be clear

scmPrtOperationOpcCleanOptions.name: scmPrtOperationOpcCleanOptions
scmPrtOperationOpcCleanOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for nopcClean in this printer.

scmPrtOperationPrintFontRequest.name: scmPrtOperationPrintFontRequest
scmPrtOperationPrintFontRequest.description: request test printing 1: pcl request 2: ps request 3: ks5843 request 4: kssm request 5: ks5895 request 6: epson requese, 7: opcClean request, 8: fuserClean request, 9: configpage request, 10: kssm request, 11: menuMap request, 12: psFlashDirectory requese,

scmPrtConfigurationPowerSave.name: scmPrtConfigurationPowerSave
scmPrtConfigurationPowerSave.description: set power save mode 1: power save mode

scmPrtConfigurationAutocont.name: scmPrtConfigurationAutocont
scmPrtConfigurationAutocont.description: It determines the printer action when the user prints a page without paper in the manual feed slot but the paper source is set to manual feed. If Auto Continue is ON the printer pick up the paper from the tray after few second. If it is OFF the printer wait forever until user insert paper into a manual feed slot.

scmPrtConfigurationJam2Recover.name: scmPrtConfigurationJam2Recover
scmPrtConfigurationJam2Recover.description: if it is on and occur JAM at Jam2 point printer will print this page again.

scmPrtConfigurationAltitudeAction.name: scmPrtConfigurationAltitudeAction
scmPrtConfigurationAltitudeAction.description: The value 'low(1)' will be used when the printer is in the low altitude location. The value 'high(2)' will be used when the printer is in the high altitude location.

scmPrtConfigurationAltitudeActionOptions.name: scmPrtConfigurationAltitudeActionOptions
scmPrtConfigurationAltitudeActionOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for altitudeAction in this printer.

scmPrtCountMediaSize.name: scmPrtCountMediaSize
scmPrtCountMediaSize.description: Paper size options that are available in this model. Some printer such like ML6060 or Modena have a 4 bytes data length. So, to distinguish these models we have to check model id or version.

scmPrtSerialNbaudRate.name: scmPrtSerialNbaudRate
scmPrtSerialNbaudRate.description: the speed when user use a serial port

scmPrtSerialBobuxonOptions.name: scmPrtSerialBobuxonOptions
scmPrtSerialBobuxonOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for robuxon in this printer.

scmPrtPCLTopMargin.name: scmPrtPCLTopMargin
scmPrtPCLTopMargin.description: Margine between top and first line of this page ,actuall value of printing is a value divided by 10. basic unit is inch. If Orientation is portrait or reverse portrait, then the range of topMargine is 0 to 99 and if Orientation is landscape or reverse landscape, then range is 0 to 170

scmPrtPCLLeftMargin.name: scmPrtPCLLeftMargin
scmPrtPCLLeftMargin.description: Left margine of printed page, actual value is a value divided by 10. Basic unit is inch. If Orentation is landscape or reverse landscape, the range is 0 to 99 and if the Orientation is portrait or reverse portrait, the range is 0 to 170.

scmPrtKS5843Sitemode.name: scmPrtKS5843Sitemode
scmPrtKS5843Sitemode.description: Each site special Mode except ksc5843 standard

scmPrtIPPColorSupported.name: scmPrtIPPColorSupported
scmPrtIPPColorSupported.description: The value of this object indicates whether the printer supports color printing.

scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsSupportedLBound.name: scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsSupportedLBound
scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsSupportedLBound.description: The value of this object gives the lower bound of the size in units of 1024 octets for jobs accepted by the printer.

scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsSupportedUBound.name: scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsSupportedUBound
scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsSupportedUBound.description: The value of this object gives the upper bound of the size in units of 1024 octets for jobs accepted by the printer.

scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsSupportedLBound.name: scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsSupportedLBound
scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsSupportedLBound.description: The value of this object gives the lower bound of the number of print images for a job.

scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsSupportedUBound.name: scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsSupportedUBound
scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsSupportedUBound.description: The value of this object gives the upper bound of the number of print images for a job.

scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsSupportedLBound.name: scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsSupportedLBound
scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsSupportedLBound.description: The value of this object gives the lower bound of the number of pages printed for a job.

scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsSupportedUBound.name: scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsSupportedUBound
scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsSupportedUBound.description: The value of this object gives the upper bound of the number of pages printed for a job.

scmPrtIPPJobSheets.name: scmPrtIPPJobSheets
scmPrtIPPJobSheets.description: The value of this object specifies the type of job start/end sheets printed with every IPP job. If the value is standard(1), the printer specific standard job start/end sheets will be printed for each job.

scmPrtIPPCollatedCopiesLBound.name: scmPrtIPPCollatedCopiesLBound
scmPrtIPPCollatedCopiesLBound.description: The value of this object gives the lower bound of the number of collated copies supported in this printer.

scmPrtIPPCollatedCopiesUBound.name: scmPrtIPPCollatedCopiesUBound
scmPrtIPPCollatedCopiesUBound.description: The value of this object gives the upper bound of the number of collated copies supported in this printer.

scmPrtIPPCollatedCopies.name: scmPrtIPPCollatedCopies
scmPrtIPPCollatedCopies.description: The value of this object gives the number of collated copies printed for the each job.

scmPrtIPPFinishingsSupported.name: scmPrtIPPFinishingsSupported
scmPrtIPPFinishingsSupported.description: The value of this object gives the type of finishings supported in the printer. If bit 1 is set, stapling is supported. If bit 2 is set, punching is supported. If bit 3 is set, covering of printed document is supported. If bit 4 is set, binding is supported. If bit 0 is set, the option of no finishings is supported.

scmPrtIPPFinishings.name: scmPrtIPPFinishings
scmPrtIPPFinishings.description: The value of this object gives the set of finishings applied for each job. If bit 0 is set, no finishings are applied. If bit 1 is set, stapling is done for each job. If bit 2 is set, punching is done for each job. If bit 3 is set, the printed document will be covered. If bit 4 is set, binding will be done for each job.

scmPrtIPPPageRangesSupported.name: scmPrtIPPPageRangesSupported
scmPrtIPPPageRangesSupported.description: The value of this object indicates whether printing only a range of pages for IPP jobs is supported. If the value is on(1), printing only specified page ranges of the given IPP job is supported.

scmPrtIPPNumberUp.name: scmPrtIPPNumberUp
scmPrtIPPNumberUp.description: The value of this object indicates the number of print images imposed on one side of a page.

scmPrtIPPNumberUpOptions.name: scmPrtIPPNumberUpOptions
scmPrtIPPNumberUpOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for numberUp in this printer.

scmPrtIPPPrintQuality.name: scmPrtIPPPrintQuality
scmPrtIPPPrintQuality.description: The value of this object indicates the print quality that the printer uses for a print job. The value draft(1) means lowest quality available on the printer. Tha value normal(2) means normal or intermediate quality on the printer. The value high(4) means highest quality available on the printer.

scmPrtIPPPrintQualityOptions.name: scmPrtIPPPrintQualityOptions
scmPrtIPPPrintQualityOptions.description: The value of this object will be the bitwise OR of the supported values for printQuality in this printer.

scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsProcessed.name: scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsProcessed
scmPrtIPPJobKOctetsProcessed.description: The value of this object gives the number of units of 1024 octets printed for the current job.

scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsCompleted.name: scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsCompleted
scmPrtIPPJobImpressionsCompleted.description: The value of this object gives the number of print images printed for the current job.

scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsCompleted.name: scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsCompleted
scmPrtIPPJobMediaSheetsCompleted.description: The value of this object gives the number of pages printed for the current job.

scmPrtConsoleDisplayBufferLcdLangType.name: scmPrtConsoleDisplayBufferLcdLangType
scmPrtConsoleDisplayBufferLcdLangType.description: Printer Console (LCD) Display String Language Type

scmPrtConsoleDisplayBufferLcdLangTypeOpt.name: scmPrtConsoleDisplayBufferLcdLangTypeOptions
scmPrtConsoleDisplayBufferLcdLangTypeOpt.description: Printer Console (LCD) Display String Language Type Option
